#: ./docs/master/pennant.md:144
msgctxt "P"
msgid "Feature classes are resolved via the [container](/docs/{{version}}/container), so you may inject dependencies into the feature class's constructor when needed."
msgstr ""

#: ./docs/10.x/pennant.md:146
#: ./docs/11.x/pennant.md:158
#: ./docs/master/pennant.md:146
msgctxt "H4"
msgid "Customizing the Stored Feature Name"
msgstr ""

#: ./docs/11.x/pennant.md:147
msgctxt "P"
msgid "If you would like to manually resolve an instance of a class based feature, you may invoke the `instance` method on the `Feature` facade:"
msgstr ""

#: ./docs/10.x/pennant.md:148
#: ./docs/11.x/pennant.md:160
#: ./docs/master/pennant.md:148
msgctxt "P"
msgid "By default, Pennant will store the feature class's fully qualified class name. If you would like to decouple the stored feature name from the application's internal structure, you may specify a `$name` property on the feature class. The value of this property will be stored in place of the class name:"
msgstr ""

#: ./docs/11.x/pennant.md:149
msgctxt "CODE: php"
msgid "use Illuminate\\Support\\Facades\\Feature;\n\n"
"$instance = Feature::instance(NewApi::class);"
msgstr ""

#: ./docs/10.x/pennant.md:150
#: ./docs/11.x/pennant.md:162
#: ./docs/master/pennant.md:150
msgctxt "CODE: php"
msgid "<?php\n\n"
"namespace App\\Features;\n\n"
"class NewApi\n"
"{\n"
"    /**\n"
"     * The stored name of the feature.\n"
"     *\n"
"     * @var string\n"
"     */\n"
"    public $name = 'new-api';\n\n"
"    // ...\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

