#: ./docs/11.x/pennant.md:1080
msgctxt "H3"
msgid "Defining Features Externally"
msgstr ""

#: ./docs/11.x/pennant.md:1082
msgctxt "P"
msgid "If your driver is a wrapper around a third-party feature flag platform, you will likely define features on the platform rather than using Pennant's `Feature::define` method. If that is the case, your custom driver should also implement the `Laravel\\Pennant\\Contracts\\DefinesFeaturesExternally` interface:"
msgstr ""

#: ./docs/11.x/pennant.md:1084
msgctxt "CODE: php"
msgid "<?php\n\n"
"namespace App\\Extensions;\n\n"
"use Laravel\\Pennant\\Contracts\\Driver;\n"
"use Laravel\\Pennant\\Contracts\\DefinesFeaturesExternally;\n\n"
"class FeatureFlagServiceDriver implements Driver, DefinesFeaturesExternally\n"
"{\n"
"    /**\n"
"     * Get the features defined for the given scope.\n"
"     */\n"
"    public function definedFeaturesForScope(mixed $scope): array {}\n\n"
"    /* ... */\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ./docs/11.x/pennant.md:1103
msgctxt "P"
msgid "The `definedFeaturesForScope` method should return a list of feature names defined for the provided scope."
msgstr ""

#: ./docs/11.x/pennant.md:1110
msgctxt "H3"
msgid "`Laravel\\Pennant\\Events\\FeatureRetrieved`"
msgstr ""

#: ./docs/11.x/pennant.md:1112
msgctxt "P"
msgid "This event is dispatched whenever a [feature is checked](#checking-features). This event may be useful for creating and tracking metrics against a feature flag's usage throughout your application."
msgstr ""

#: ./docs/11.x/pennant.md:1114
msgctxt "H3"
msgid "`Laravel\\Pennant\\Events\\FeatureResolved`"
msgstr ""

#: ./docs/11.x/pennant.md:1116
msgctxt "P"
msgid "This event is dispatched the first time a feature's value is resolved for a specific scope."
msgstr ""

#: ./docs/11.x/pennant.md:1118
msgctxt "H3"
msgid "`Laravel\\Pennant\\Events\\UnknownFeatureResolved`"
msgstr ""

#: ./docs/11.x/pennant.md:1120
msgctxt "P"
msgid "This event is dispatched the first time an unknown feature is resolved for a specific scope. Listening to this event may be useful if you have intended to remove a feature flag but have accidentally left stray references to it throughout your application:"
msgstr ""

#: ./docs/11.x/pennant.md:1122
msgctxt "CODE: php"
msgid "<?php\n\n"
"namespace App\\Providers;\n\n"
"use Illuminate\\Support\\ServiceProvider;\n"
"use Illuminate\\Support\\Facades\\Event;\n"
"use Illuminate\\Support\\Facades\\Log;\n"
"use Laravel\\Pennant\\Events\\UnknownFeatureResolved;\n\n"
"class AppServiceProvider extends ServiceProvider\n"
"{\n"
"    /**\n"
"     * Bootstrap any application services.\n"
"     */\n"
"    public function boot(): void\n"
"    {\n"
"        Event::listen(function (UnknownFeatureResolved $event) {\n"
"            Log::error(\"Resolving unknown feature [{$event->feature}].\");\n"
"        });\n"
"    }\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ./docs/11.x/pennant.md:1146
msgctxt "H3"
msgid "`Laravel\\Pennant\\Events\\DynamicallyRegisteringFeatureClass`"
msgstr ""

#: ./docs/11.x/pennant.md:1148
msgctxt "P"
msgid "This event is dispatched when a [class based feature](#class-based-features) is dynamically checked for the first time during a request."
msgstr ""

#: ./docs/11.x/pennant.md:1150
msgctxt "H3"
msgid "`Laravel\\Pennant\\Events\\UnexpectedNullScopeEncountered`"
msgstr ""

#: ./docs/11.x/pennant.md:1152
msgctxt "P"
msgid "This event is dispatched when a `null` scope is passed to a feature definition that [doesn't support null](#nullable-scope)."
msgstr ""

#: ./docs/11.x/pennant.md:1154
msgctxt "P"
msgid "This situation is handled gracefully and the feature will return `false`. However, if you would like to opt out of this feature's default graceful behavior, you may register a listener for this event in the `boot` method of your application's `AppServiceProvider`:"
msgstr ""

#: ./docs/11.x/pennant.md:1156
msgctxt "CODE: php"
msgid "use Illuminate\\Support\\Facades\\Log;\n"
"use Laravel\\Pennant\\Events\\UnexpectedNullScopeEncountered;\n\n"
"/**\n"
" * Bootstrap any application services.\n"
" */\n"
"public function boot(): void\n"
"{\n"
"    Event::listen(UnexpectedNullScopeEncountered::class, fn () => abort(500));\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ./docs/11.x/pennant.md:1170
msgctxt "H3"
msgid "`Laravel\\Pennant\\Events\\FeatureUpdated`"
msgstr ""

#: ./docs/11.x/pennant.md:1172
msgctxt "P"
msgid "This event is dispatched when updating a feature for a scope, usually by calling `activate` or `deactivate`."
msgstr ""

